# ğŸ•·ï¸ SPIDER  
_A recursive image downloader and web crawler._

---

## ğŸ§  What It Does

**SPIDER** crawls through a website starting from a given URL and downloads all the image files it finds.  
If the `-r` option is enabled, it will recursively follow links on the site up to a given depth.

---

## ğŸ”§ Features

- Extracts and downloads images (`.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.png`, `.gif`, `.bmp`)
- Optionally follows links to crawl deeper into websites
- Saves images into a custom or default folder (`./data`)
- Uses BeautifulSoup to parse HTML
- Filters duplicate visits with `visited_urls` set

---

## ğŸš€ Usage

```bash
python3 ./spider [options] URL


# ğŸ¦‚ SCORPION  
_A command-line EXIF metadata viewer for images._

---

## ğŸ§  What It Does

**SCORPION** is a Python tool that extracts and displays **EXIF metadata** from image files (like `.jpg`). It provides technical details about how and where a photo was taken â€” including camera make/model, exposure, ISO, GPS coordinates, and more.

---

## ğŸ§¾ Features

- Displays **image format**, size, and mode
- Shows **camera information** (make, model, orientation)
- Reads **camera settings** (ISO, flash, exposure time, f-number)
- Extracts **GPS location data** (latitude, longitude, Google Maps link)
- Lists **software info**, EXIF version, white balance, and metering mode
- Gracefully handles missing or corrupt EXIF data

---

## ğŸš€ Usage

```bash
python3 ./scorpion IMAGE1 [IMAGE2 ...]

